  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "A more advanced collaborative pattern leverages LLM-generated unit tests themselves as a high-quality feedback signal or reward model, used to evaluate and filter the outputs of other code generation tasks.",
    "This approach can even dynamically adjust the number of generated tests based on problem difficulty to optimize evaluation efficiency [91].",
    "Furthermore, LLMs can not only operate in parallel with traditional tools but also serve as their intelligent front-end.",
    "For example, research has utilized LLMs as intelligent filters, first extracting massive candidate test inputs from bug reports via traditional methods, then using the LLM's powerful semantic understanding to identify the most relevant parts, and finally providing these high-quality seed inputs to search-based tools like EvoSuite, thereby significantly enhancing their fault detection capabilities [105].",
    "RQ2 Key InsightThe Iterative Feedback Loop is the essential component of practical systems: Among all enhancement techniques, the post-generation iterative validation-feedbackrefinement loop has proven to be the most impactful technical pattern to date."
  ],
